cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.SE, cs.LG 

This paper discusses the modeling of adaptive strategies of an intelligent actor against an active cyber defensive system, which falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CR). The use of genetic algorithms to evolve strategies is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the study of strategic considerations and balancing rewards against complexity is a topic in both social intelligence (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the simulation results presented in the paper involve optimization and fitness evaluation, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
